==Dickson Prize in Science== The Dickson Prize in Science is awarded annually by [[Carnegie Mellon University]], and recognizes those who "have made the most progress in the scientific field in the United States for the year in question."<ref name=CMUAward>{{cite web|title=The Dickson Prize in Science|url=http://www.cmu.edu/dickson-prize/about-the-prize/index.html|publisher=Carnegie Mellon University|accessdate=4 June 2015}}</ref> The award is dated by the year in which it was announced, which is often the year before the lecture occurs.<ref name=CMUList>{{cite web|title=Dickson Prize Past Winners|url=http://www.cmu.edu/dickson-prize/past-winners/|publisher=Carnegie Mellon University|accessdate=4 June 2015}}</ref>
