{{Infobox language |name=Mozabite |altname=تونژابت |nativename=''Tumẓabt''"TunŻabt" |states=[[Algeria]] |region=[[M'zab]] (''[[wilaya]]'' of [[Ghardaïa Province|Ghardaïa]]) |ethnicity=[[Mozabite people|Mozabite]] |speakers=150,000 |date=2010 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Afro-Asiatic |fam2=[[Berber languages|Berber]] |fam3=[[Northern Berber languages|Northern]] |fam4=[[Zenati languages|Zenati]] |fam5=[[Mzab–Wargla languages|Mzab–Wargla]] |script=[[Arabic alphabet]], [[Tifinagh]], [[Berber Latin alphabet]] |iso3=mzb |glotto=tumz1238 |glottorefname=Tumzabt |map=Mzab-Wargla Berberophone areas.PNG |mapcaption=Berber-speaking areas of the Mzab, Ouargla, and Oued Righ }}
'''Mozabite''', or '''Tunżabt''', is a [[Berber languages|Berber]] dialect spoken by the [[Mozabite people|Mozabites]], an [[Ibadi]] [[Berbers|Berber]] group inhabiting the seven cities of the [[M'zab]] natural region in the northern [[Sahara]]n [[Algeria]]. It is also spoken by small numbers of Mozabite emigrants in other local cities and elsewhere. Mozabite is one of the [[Mzab–Wargla languages]], a dialect cluster of the [[Zenati languages]]. It is very closely related to the nearby Berber dialects of [[Ouargla]] and [[Oued Righ Berber|Oued Righ]] as well as the more distant [[Gourara]].
==Bibliography== * ابراهيم و بكير عبد السلام. الوجيز في قواعد الكتابة و النحو للغة الأمازيغية "المزابية". المطبعة العرببة: غرداية 1996. * Delheure, Jean. ''Aǧraw n Yiwalen Tumẓabt d-Tefṛansist = Dictionnaire Mozabite–Francais''. SELAF:Paris 1984.
