{{other uses|Nashi (disambiguation)}} {{Infobox organization | name = Nashi | bgcolor = <!-- header background color --> | fgcolor = <!-- header text color --> | image = | image_border = | size = <!-- default 200px --> | alt = <!-- alt text; see [[WP:ALT]] --> | caption = | map = <!-- optional --> | msize = <!-- map size, optional, default 250px --> | malt = <!-- map alt text --> | mcaption = <!-- optional --> | map2 = | abbreviation = | motto = | predecessor = | successor = | formation = | extinction = <!-- date of extinction, optional --> | type = [[International nongovernmental organization|INGO]] | status = <!-- ad hoc, treaty, foundation, etc --> | purpose = To [[List of organizations opposing human trafficking|oppose human trafficking]] by [[Consciousness raising|raising awareness]] through education | headquarters = | location = [[Saskatoon]], [[Saskatchewan]], [[Canada]] | coords = <!-- Coordinates of location using a coordinates template --> | region_served = [[Ukraine]] | membership = | language = [[English language|English]] | general = <!-- Secretary General --> | leader_title = President | leader_name = Savelia Curniski | leader_title2 = | leader_name2 = | leader_title3 = | leader_name3 = | leader_title4 = | leader_name4 = | key_people = Betty Lawrence | main_organ = <!-- gral. assembly, board of directors, etc --> | parent_organization = <!-- if one --> | affiliations = [[Public Service Alliance of Canada]] | budget = | num_staff = | num_volunteers = | website = [http://www.nashi.ca/ nashi.ca] | remarks = | former name = }}
'''Nashi''' ({{lang-uk|Наші}}; ''Nashi''; "Ours") is a [[Saskatoon]], [[Saskatchewan]], [[Canada]]-based [[List of organizations opposing human trafficking|organisation that opposes human trafficking]] by [[Consciousness raising|raising awareness]] through education.<ref>{{Cite journal|journal=[[Shaw TV#Saskatoon|Shaw TV Saskatoon]]|title=Arts & Entertainment|author=Curtis Anderson|date=June 2, 2012}}</ref> Savelia Curniski is the president of NASHI.<ref>{{Cite journal|journal=Discover Moose Jaw|title=Human Trafficking Discussed|date=March 13, 2009|url=http://www.discovermoosejaw.com/component/content/article?id=7607:human-trafficking-discussed&Itemid=534|accessdate=November 9, 2015}}</ref> The organisation has established a [[vocational school]] in [[Lviv]], [[Ukraine]] to teach girls and women [[carpentry]], [[sewing]], [[information processing]], and [[cooking]] so they won't become trapped in [[Human trafficking in Ukraine|Ukraine's human trafficking network]].<ref>{{Cite journal|journal=[[The StarPhoenix]]|title=Group battles to prevent Ukraine sex trafficking|date=May 26, 2006|url=http://www.canada.com/story_print.html?id=8cbae4a1-ae25-4b49-974a-6b21efac4b78&sponsor=|archive-url=https://archive.is/20130118180135/http://www.canada.com/story_print.html?id=8cbae4a1-ae25-4b49-974a-6b21efac4b78&sponsor=|dead-url=yes|archive-date=January 18, 2013|accessdate=September 14, 2012}}</ref> NASHI also founded the Maple Leaf Centre, a resource centre and [[Shelter (building)|shelter]] in Ukraine for young people who are at risk of being trafficked.<ref>{{Cite journal|journal=Saskatoonhomepage.ca|title=Conference Focuses on Human Trafficking|date=October 17, 2009|url=http://www.saskatoonhomepage.ca/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=21349&Itemid=421|accessdate=September 14, 2012}}</ref> In 2011, NASHI hosted the Saskatoon portion of the Canada Freedom Relay to raise awareness about [[human trafficking]].<ref>{{Cite journal|journal=Saskatoonhomepage.ca|title=Freedom Relay Kicks Off Today|author=Edwin Dewaal|date=September 25, 2011|url=http://www.saskatoonhomepage.ca/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=35242&Itemid=421|accessdate=September 14, 2012}}</ref> The event lasted 45 minutes and raised funds for various programs that aid human trafficking victims.<ref>{{Cite journal|journal=[[The StarPhoenix]]|date=September 13, 2012|title=Special Events|url=https://thestarphoenix.com/EventsVENTS/7234526/story.html|accessdate=September 14, 2012}}</ref> In 2012, NASHI organised the Youth Unchained conference in Saskatoon that presented approximately 900 youth with information about human trafficking.<ref>{{Cite journal|journal=Prairie Messenger|title=Youth Unchained fights human trafficking|author=Kiply Lukan Yaworski|url=http://www.prairiemessenger.ca/05_30_2012/unchained_05_30_12.html|accessdate=September 14, 2012}}</ref> Betty Lawrence is one of the co-founders of NASHI.<ref>{{Cite journal|journal=Saskatoonhomepage.ca|title=Nashi Harvest Brunch|date=October 23, 2008|url=http://www.saskatoonhomepage.ca/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=14535&Itemid=374|accessdate=September 14, 2012}}</ref> The organisation's activities are facilitated by volunteers.<ref>{{Cite journal|journal=[[The StarPhoenix]]|author=Ann Adam|date=May 2, 2012|title=Event tackles issue of human trafficking|url=http://www2.canada.com/saskatoonstarphoenix/news/local/story.html?id=ed9641f6-b911-4890-91a9-bcfbea253c27|accessdate=September 14, 2012}}</ref>
