{{Infobox language |name = Puelche |nativename = ''Gününa Küne'' |altname = Gennaken |states = [[Argentina]] |extinct = 1934 |ref=e18 |speakers2 = with the death of Trruúlmani |familycolor = American |fam1 = [[Chonan languages|Chonan]] ? |fam2 = Puelche–Het ? |iso3 = pue |glotto = puel1244 |glottorefname= Puelche |notice=IPA }}
'''Puelche''' is an extinct language formerly spoken by the [[Puelche people]] in the [[Pampa]]s region of [[Argentina]]. The language is also known as ''Gününa Küne'', Gennaken (Guenaken), Northern Tehuelche, ''Gününa Yajich'', Ranquelche, and Pampa.
== Classification == Puelche has long been considered a [[language isolate]]. Based on very limited evidence, Viegas Barros (1992) suggests that Puelche might be closely related to the language of the [[Querandí]], one of the [[Het peoples]], and Viegas Barros (2005) that it is related to the [[Chon languages]].<ref>Campbell, Lyle. (in preparation) "The classification of South American languages''. In Campbell & Grondona (eds.), ''South America''. Mouton de Gruyter.</ref> Further afield, inclusion in a putative [[Macro-Jibaro]] family has been posited.
== Phonology ==
=== Vowels === Puelche has 7 [[vowel]]s:<ref name="clairis1997">{{cite journal | last = Clairis | first = Christos | authorlink = Christos Clairis | year = 1997 | title = Lingüística Fueguina 1997 | journal = Onomázein | volume = 2 | pages = 421–450}}</ref>
{| class="wikitable" |- align=center ! rowspan="2" | ! [[Front vowel|Front]] ! colspan="2" | [[Back vowel|Back]] |- align=center ! <small>Unrounded</small> ! <small>Unrounded</small> ! <small>Rounded</small> |- align=center ! [[Close vowel|Close]] | {{IPA|i}} | | {{IPA|u}} |- align=center ! [[Close-mid vowel|Close-mid]] | {{IPA|e}} | {{IPA|ɤ}} | {{IPA|o}} |- align=center ! [[Open-mid vowel|Open-mid]] | | {{IPA|ʌ}} | |- align=center ! [[Open vowel|Open]] | {{IPA|a}} | | |}
=== Consonants === Puelche has 25 [[consonant]]s:<ref name="clairis1997" />
