{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2017}} {{Use Indian English|date=March 2017}} {{Infobox language |name=Rathwi |nativename=Bareli |region= |ethnicity=[[Bhil people|Bhil]] |speakers={{sigfig|101,000|2}} |date=2001 census |ref=e18 |familycolor=Indo-European |fam2=[[Indo-Iranian languages|Indo-Iranian]] |fam3=[[Indo-Aryan languages|Indo-Aryan]] |fam4=[[Western Indo-Aryan languages|Western Indo-Aryan]] |fam5=[[Bhil languages|Bhil]] |fam6=Bareli |script=[[Gujarati alphabet|Gujarati]] |iso3=bgd |glotto=rath1242 |glottorefname=Rathwi Bareli }}
'''Rathwi Bareli''' is a [[Bhil languages|Bhil language]] of India. It is close to two other languages called Bareli, but not mutually intelligible with them. It has 81%–93% lexical similarity with Rathwi Bareli dialects, 67%–73% with Palya Bareli and 68%–79% with Pauri Bareli.<ref>{{e19|bgd}}</ref>
