{{distinguish|Zoroastrian Dari language}} {{Infobox language |name=Gabri |nativename=Southern Gabri |states=[[Chad]] |region= |speakers={{sigfig|34400|2}} |date=2000 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Afro-Asiatic |fam2=[[Chadic languages|Chadic]] |fam3=[[East Chadic languages|East Chadic]] |fam4=[[East Chadic A languages|East Chadic A]] |fam5=[[Gabri languages]] (A.2.2) |iso3=gab |glotto=gabr1253 |glottorefname=Gabri |dia1=Buruwa |dia2=Darbe |dia3=Moonde }}
'''Gabri''', sometimes disambiguated from related languages also called "Gabri" as '''Southern Gabri''', is an [[East Chadic languages|East Chadic]] [[dialect cluster]] spoken in the [[Tandjilé Region]] of [[Chad]]. The principal varieties are Buruwa, Darbe (Dormon), and Moonde.
