'''''The Inner House''''' is a novel by [[Walter Besant]] published in 1888. It is set a few centuries in the future and is a [[List of dystopian literature|dystopian fantasy]] about a society which has reached a stage of inert uniformity under the control of an elite group of scientists who have discovered an elixir of immortality. The plot follows a rebel group which wishes to restore the more exciting conditions of nineteenth-century life. It has been described as an anticipation of [[Aldous Huxley]]'s ''[[Brave New World]]''.<ref>Carla Maria Gnappi, Science and Technology in Victorian Utopias (victorianweb.org).</ref>

